overview: The user initiated a request to fix numerous issues within a pull
  request, highlighting critical Vercel deployment failures. The agent embarked
  on a comprehensive debugging and fixing process. This involved resolving
  initial linting errors, addressing a critical security vulnerability by
  implementing HMAC-signed session tokens compatible with Vercel's Edge Runtime,
  and enhancing data handling with pagination and robust input validation.
  Significant effort was dedicated to resolving Vercel deployment issues, which
  necessitated updating Next.js to address a CVE, adapting Prisma configurations
  for version 7, and overhauling ESLint setup due to breaking changes in Next.js
  16. A key decision was to lazy-load the Prisma client to prevent build-time
  connection errors. Ultimately, while most code-related issues were resolved,
  the final Vercel deployment failures were traced back to unconfigured
  environment variables on the Vercel platform, for which the agent provided
  clear instructions to the user.
